<html><head></head><body><b>Christian Johann Doppler (1803-1853)</b>
<br/>An Austrian astronomer <br/>and physicist, was professor at the university in Vienna. <br/>He discovered and explained the phenomenon characterised by a change <br/>in the apparent frequency <br/>of a wave as a result <br/>of relative motion <br/>(the Doppler effect). <br/>He is also the author <br/>of numerous works in optics and instrumental astronomy.
</body></html>